[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: GHOST Metrics, Evaluation, and Benchmarking Requirements
UID: GHOST-MET
VERSION: 0.1-draft
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text
  AUTO_LEVELS: On
  NODE_IN_TOC: True

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 1. Purpose

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Defines current Metrics tab demo boundary and future real metrics backend, including token usage, cost, latency, retrieval counts, memory diagnostics, A3/A4 quality evaluation, SPLADE/ReRanker evaluation, benchmark datasets, and regression checks.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 2. Scope and Boundary

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MET-ROOT
TITLE: GHOST Metrics, Evaluation, and Benchmarking Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
This file is a draft child requirement file in the GHOST StrictDoc requirement tree.

It defines ownership, scope, and placeholder headings for this capability area. Detailed atomic requirements shall be migrated here from legacy requirements, implementation status, architecture notes, UML files, and code evidence after human approval.

This file shall not duplicate detailed requirements owned by sibling files.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-QGO-ROOT

